name: THE AHOOL
description: The ahool, so named because it makes a long "ahOOOooool" sound, is said to be shaped like a bat, and is described as being the size of a one-year-old child with a giant wingspan of approximately 12 feet. described as short-haired, dark gray, has large black eyes, flattened supporting arms, leathery wings and a monkey-like head, a human-like face with a flattened face. Often seen squatting in the forest, with the wings closed and tightly on the body of Ahool, his legs are seen to point backwards (upside down). It is thought that Ahool is a nocturnal being
